## Memorizing and recognizing ex falso

These next proofs are designed to help you do ex falso, which we cover in the second lecture from this week. These proofs are intended to be very short, all under 5 lines beyond the assumptions.

<br>
<br>

*Example 11*.

```{.ProofChecker .GamutIPND submission="none"}
 a, a->⊥ :|-: b
|a :assumption
|a->⊥ :assumption
```

<br>
<br>

*Example 12*.

```{.ProofChecker .GamutIPND submission="none"}
 a, b, b->~a :|-: c
|a :assumption
|b :assumption
|b->~a :assumption
```

*Example 13*.

```{.ProofChecker .GamutIPND submission="none"}
 a/\b, c/\~b :|-: d
|a/\b :assumption
|c/\~b :assumption
```

*Example 14*.

On this one, resist the inclination to do an arrow introduction, and focus rather on finding a contradiction among the assumptions and then doing ex falso.

```{.ProofChecker .GamutIPND submission="none"}
 a->b, ~(a->b) :|-: a->c
|a->b :assumption
|~(a->b) :assumption
```

*Example 15*.

This one is just practice with the repeat rule.

```{.ProofChecker .GamutIPND submission="none"}
  :|-: q->q
```




