## Proofs with ex falso

These are simple proofs with ex falso and the other rules which we have available.

<br>
<br>

*Example 16*.

```{.ProofChecker .GamutIPND submission="none"}
 ~a :|-: a->b
|~a :assumption
```

<br>
<br>

*Example 17*.

```{.ProofChecker .GamutIPND submission="none"}
 ~a :|-: a->b
|~a :assumption
```

<br>
<br>

*Example 18*.

```{.ProofChecker .GamutIPND submission="none"}
 a :|-: ~a->b
|~a :assumption
```

*Example 19*.

This is one half of the classical equivalence of a material conditional with a certain kind of disjunction. Hint: you need to do a disjunction elimination on the premise. One of the arrow statements can be justified via the repeat rule like in Example 19.

```{.ProofChecker .GamutIPND submission="none"}
 ~p\/q :|-: p->q
|~p\/q :assumption
```

*Example 20*.

```{.ProofChecker .GamutIPND submission="none"}
 p->q, ~q\/q :|-: ~p\/q
|p->q :assumption
|~q\/q :assumption
```



